'''研究著作法案（英语：Research Works Act）''', 又称 H.R. 3699, 是一项美国的[[法案|法案]]。该法案于2011年12月16日由议员[[Darrell_Issa|Darrell Issa]] (R-CA) 提交[[美国美国众议院|美国美国众议院]]，并由[[Carolyn_B._Maloney|Carolyn B. Maloney]] (D-NY)共同支持。此法案所包含的条款可以妨碍对由美国联邦所资助的研究项目实行的“强制要求開放獲取”（英语：open access mandate）。<ref name=sparc>{{cite web|last=Joseph|first=Heather|title=Take Action: Oppose H.R. 3699, a new bill to block public access to publicly funded research|url=http://www.arl.org/sparc/media/blog/12-0106.shtml|work=SPARC blog|accessdate=January 8, 2012|date=January 6, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120123075750/http://www.arl.org/sparc/media/blog/12-0106.shtml|archive-date=2012-01-23|dead-url=yes}}</ref> 它实质上要更改<ref name="ALA">[http://www.districtdispatch.org/2012/01/trying-to-roll-back-the-clock-on-open-access-research-works-act-introduced/ Trying to roll back the clock on Open Access] {{Wayback|url=http://www.districtdispatch.org/2012/01/trying-to-roll-back-the-clock-on-open-access-research-works-act-introduced/ |date=20120116224428 }} statement by the [[American_Library_Association|American Library Association]] that "vehemently ''opposes'' the bill".</ref> [[國立衛生研究院_(美國)|国立卫生研究院]]的[[公共访问政策|公共访问政策]] （英语：Public Access Policy）中所规定的由纳税人所资助的研究项目应该可以在网络上自由地访问到的主张。<ref>{{cite news|last=Dobbs|first=David|title=Congress Considers Paywalling Science You Already Paid For|url=http://www.wired.com/wiredscience/2012/01/congress-considers-paywalling-science-you-already-paid-for/|newspaper=Wired|date=January 6, 2012|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/64cQ2CPft?url=http://www.wired.com/wiredscience/2012/01/congress-considers-paywalling-science-you-already-paid-for/|archivedate=2012年1月11日|deadurl=no}}</ref> 如果这项法案被通过，它将严重地阻碍科学[[数据|数据]]的自由共享。<ref>Piwowar, Heather. [http://researchremix.wordpress.com/2012/01/07/rwa-data/ Research Works Act Attacks Data Dissemination Too] {{Wayback|url=http://researchremix.wordpress.com/2012/01/07/rwa-data/ |date=20120114082204 }}</ref>
